(count) |\n| Scalar filter broadcasts | `\\bflw\\b|\\bfld\\b` (count) |\n| Tail residue | second `vsetvli` with runtime AVL after main body |\n\nReport raw counts, not approximations. For LMUL, state the exact `e32,mN` form.\n\n## Gatekeeper\n\nIf (LMUL=m8 in hot loop) AND (no spills) AND (vle:fma <= 1) AND (prior 2+ rounds regressed/neutral): output `\"no clear opportunity\"` instead of a proposal. For round 1 (no history), you will almost certainly propose something - only skip if the baseline is already provably optimal.\n\n## Divisibility rules (hard)\n\nFor `tile_sizes` matrix with L=4 levels, R=7 rank:\n- Level 0 non-zero tile_sizes[0][d] MUST divide iteration_space[d]\n- At level i>=1, non-zero tile_sizes[i][d] MUST divide the nearest previous non-zero parent; if none, it must divide iteration_space[d]\n- `0` at tile_sizes[i][d] = skip tiling at this level (always valid)\n- Matrix shape must be exactly 4x7\n\nIteration space: `[1, 112, 112, 32, 3, 3, 3]` = [N, OH, OW, OF, KH, KW, IC]\nParallel dims: [0,1,2,3] = N, OH, OW, OF\nReduction dims: [4,5,6] = KH, KW, IC\n\nDefault tile_sizes (distribution/parallel_inner/reduction/identity):\n- L0: [0, 16, 56, 32, 0, 0, 0]     (workgroup)\n- L1: [1, 1, 8, 32, 0, 0, 0]       (vector parallel)\n- L2: [0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 3]        (reduction)\n- L3: [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]        (identity)\n\n## LMUL arithmetic\n\nVLmax(LMUL) = VLEN_bits * LMUL / SEW_bits\nFor VLEN=1024, SEW=32: m1=32, m2=64, m4=128, m8=256.\n\nInnermost vectorized parallel dim for conv_2d_nhwc_hwcf is the OF axis (dim 3). Its parent extent at L1 comes from L0[3]=32, so the OF inner tile has ceiling of 32. L1[3]=32 already fills VLmax at m1 exactly. To push higher LMUL on OF you'd need L0[3] >= VLmax(next_LMUL), but OF extent overall = 32, so m2 would require L0[3]=64 > OF extent. **OF is already LMUL-saturated at m1=32 on this dispatch.**\n\nTherefore LMUL cannot be raised on the OF axis. The remaining degrees of freedom are: widen the inner parallel tile on OW (dim 2) to amortize filter broadcasts; or raise the reduction tile on KH/KW (dims 4,5). Current L2 reduction tile is [1,1,3] meaning KH=1, KW=1, IC=3 per reduction step - KH and KW are already at 1 (minimum productive), IC=3 is full (IC extent = 3). So reduction is already fully tiled at IC and minimally chunked on KH/KW.\n\nStrategy candidates for round 1:\n- A. Widen L1 OW from 8 to 16 (112 % 16 = 0, OW parent at L0 = 56, 56 % 16 != 0 - INVALID). Re-check: L0[2]=56, so inner OW tile must divide 56. Divisors of 56: 1,2,4,7,8,14,28,56. 16 NOT in list. Try 14: 56/14=4 (valid), 7: 56/7=8 (valid), 28: 56/28=2 (valid), 56 (valid).\n- B. Raise reduction L2 KH or KW from 1 to 3 (full extent). KH extent 3, KW extent 3. 3/3=1 so 3 divides 3.\n- C. Shrink L0 OW 56->28 and widen L1 OW 8->14 or L1 OW->28.\n- D. Raise L1 OH from 1 to a divisor of L0 OH=16 (e.g. 2, 4, 8, 16) to enlarge output register footprint on height axis.\n\nReconcile your choice with the asm evidence. Cite the exact flw count, vle count, vfmacc count, and observed LMUL.\n\n## Output\n\nEmit ONE JSON object exactly matching this schema, or the string `\"no clear opportunity\"`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"tile_sizes\": [[...], [...], [...], [...]],\n  \"move\": \"short_tag\",\n  \"rationale\": \"1-3 sentences citing asm evidence + chosen move + expected asm-observable change\",\n  \"divisibility_check\": \"pass\",\n  \"expected_asm_change\": \"what to look for in next round's asm\"\n}\n```\n\nVerify divisibility manually before emitting. Report in your final message: (1) the raw asm metrics you extracted, (2) the proposal JSON, (3) the divisibility verification for each non-zero entry."},"uuid":"978bfae4-2df9-4a67-87e1-1b99626d4b25","timestamp":"2026-04-20T11:17:41.860Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/nick/work/AutoIREE","sessionId":"6444719a-e5e6-48c0-81ce-3dae64478e3f","version":"2.1.114","gitBranch":"main","slug":"silly-herding-ripple"}
